column5: Got out for a quick couple of hours on Saturday night on Lake Muskoka.  Thanks to the expert guidance of a friend who knows his way around out there, I iced this beauty 25.5" eye.  Hit a live minnow on a green jig that was next to me while I jigged an orange chubby darter.  Quite possibly the largest fish I've ever pulled through the ice....definitely the biggest eye    I would have a much lengthier report about my travels the following day to Trout Creek and surrounding area....but it was a bit of a skunk-fest....so it's best left undisclosed
A real beauty! Congrats to you!
She's gorgious!!  Congrats on your PB and landing that thing. WOW
Good job man.  Congrats on your PB!!

Ben -- I swear I was using my Lindy Darter first....but I was told that orange was the go-to colour, and the only orange darter I had was a salmo   Still no fish on that thing...but the Lindy is getting scuffed up nicely
Way to go !!! Shes a real beauty Dud !!!
Congrats on your PB johnnyb Your grin in the pic says it all
